data.title: Louis IX of France
data.meta_description: Louis IX also called Saint Louis, was King of France from 1226 to his death. He established the Parlement of Paris. After his death he was canonised in 1297 by Pope Boniface VIII. He was a patron saint of barbers, France, groomers, button makers, sculptors.
data.text: Louis IX (25 April 1214 â€“ 25 August 1270) also called Saint Louis, was King of France from 1226 to his death. He established the Parlement of Paris. After his death he was canonised (declared a saint) in 1297 by Pope Boniface VIII. He was a patron saint of barbers, France, groomers, button makers, sculptors.
